name: thorns
description:
growing up, my mother loved roses. i remember thinking that she loved them more than she ever loved me. and so, as a child, i choked and choked and choked on thorns, the thorns of her beloved roses she spent so much time nurturing -- 

she never gave any of that nurturing to me. 

and still i choke and choke and choke. 

and i paint and paint and paint and it never chases away that pain. i poured myself out in the paint, and yet still --

it hurts,
and i choke --

perhaps i will always choke.

it's okay. it's all i've ever known.
